This paper deals with anomaly detection using generative adversarial networks and Gaussian mixture models in human mobility data. The paper involves deep learning techniques and focuses on the development of a new algorithm for multimodal anomaly detection. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
